# BharatCMS - India-First Headless CMS

## Tech Stack
- Strapi v4.25.x with TypeScript
- PostgreSQL (Supabase)
- Cloudflare R2 storage
- Razorpay payments
- Groq AI
- Resend email
- WhatsApp Cloud API

## Architecture Rules
- All custom features go in src/plugins/
- Never modify Strapi core (/node_modules/@strapi/)
- Use TypeScript strict mode
- Indian context: ₹ currency, GST, Hindi support
- Multi-tenant ready (workspace field on entities)

## DON'T
- Don't suggest Stripe (use Razorpay)
- Don't use AWS S3 (use Cloudflare R2)
- Don't use OpenAI directly (use Groq for cost)
- Don't modify Strapi core code

## DO
- Use Strapi factories pattern
- Write GST-aware logic (CGST/SGST/IGST)
- Format prices as ₹X,XX,XXX (Indian style)
- Use TypeScript types from Strapi
- Add error handling with strapi.log

## Current Phase
Phase: 1 (Rebrand)
Task: 1.2

## File Conventions
- Plugins: kebab-case (razorpay-service.ts)
- Components: PascalCase (AIButton.tsx)
- Content types: lowercase (product, order)
- Routes: kebab-case (/create-order)
